The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 10: A sharp slowdown in the mining sector lowered industrial growth to 7.4 per cent during August 2005 against 8.6 per cent in the same month last fiscal. Growth in the mining sector declined to a negative 1.3 per cent during the month compared with 4.4 per cent in August last fiscal. Manufacturing growth slowed down as well to 8.2 per cent from 9.1 per cent a year ago.

 New Delhi, Oct. 10: The government today put in place contingency plans to ensure smooth telecom services as the deadline given by department of telecommunication expired for a response from over 2,200 top technical officials to take position about their repatriation from MTNL and BSNL to a surplus cell.

 Mumbai, Oct. 10: Colgate-Palmolive has won a round of legal battle against Ajanta India by getting a court to restrain the latter from passing off its product as that of Colgate Dental cream. Modifying its earlier interim order of March 2003, Delhi High Court recently directed Ajanta to modify its package to clearly distinguish its product from that of its competitor, Colgate-Palmolive (India) said.

 New Delhi, Oct. 10: British oil major BP plc will this week sign an agreement with Hindustan Petroleum Corp (HPCL) to initiate a dialogue for picking up a stake in HPCL?s Rs 12,000-crore Bhatinda refinery in Punjab. 




